channel.title: The laptop
channel.description:
Ok, I just bought my laptop and I'm fucking amazed, the speed, the power, just amazing.
So, now that I got to play with it for a couple of hours it's time to see what it's limits are.
For more information about "it", look [url=http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,512309.0.html]here[/url].
In order for that, I'm looking for some of the best games, so I thought let me ask the community of moparscape.
I would like to receive a top 10 of you favorite games that got high-end graphics, since I have never been able to play these sorts of games I do not know what is and what isn't good.
Thank you for your time, and all normal posts are very much appreciated.

@MistaBigBoss wrote:

There’s a little light next to the camera, wich is physically atached to the camera as in, whenever it sends video data the light turns on (not controlled by software). Wich indicates when the webcam is on or not, and indeed you really have to be stupid to get someone to tap your cam.

Also, by heart, I mean the processor, a computer can work without a GPU, but without the CPU (heart) it does not work because it processes all the data just like the heart pumps all the blood in our body. I thought that one out myself.

item.title: The laptop
item.dc:creator: @SilentCJ SilentCJ
item.description:
@SilentCJ wrote:

[quote=“MistaBigBoss, post:14, topic:411273”][quote author=SilentCJ link=topic=512538.msg3722136#msg3722136 date=1314014926]
Don’t expect it to run everything smoothly as it’s only a laptop, I’m a laptop gamer too, and the specs of mine are very slightly below this, however my mate owns the same graphics card and processor, just with a different brand machine.
You’ll still only be running crysis 2 in low at 40fps believe me

If you wanna see benchmarks for your card here: http://www.notebookcheck.net/NVIDIA-GeForce-GT-540M.41715.0.html
[/quote]Thanks for that site, very interesting stuff there.

Also, bought the laptop (edit: just noticed that i already mentioned that) and I’m at 65% of the Crysis 2 single campain on soldier difficulty.

My average fps rates don’t match that site’s benchmark rates tough. For example, when playing Crysis 2 on high detail and 800 x 600 gives me an average of 90 fps.

Crysis 2 on high and 1280 x 720 wich I use as my standard for Crysis 2 gives me 50 average fps.

My laptop’s native resolution is 1600 x 900 (16:9) so when I play at 1280 x 720 (wich is also 16:9) I bearly notice a difference, expect for the higher fps rate.

I guess I can thank my quad core i7 for these rates.[/quote]
‘High’ as in the lowest setting? Crysis 2 doesn’t have a lower setting does it, just high, extra high, hardcore and ultra iirc.
I imagine it looked pretty shitty on 800x600 eh
Yeah I use the 1280x720 when I play and that runs fine, as I have the same native resolution as you.

Read full topic
